	<p>
    <div style="clear:both;"></div><a href="http://weblog.infoworld.com/udell/2004/05/10.html#a993">Jon Udell: How Much Is That Data Model in the Window?</a>.&nbsp; This is a nice addition to the discussion of XML providing a data model or not.&nbsp; The audio interview with John Shewchuk is interesting, as is Jon's wresting with the assertion that there isn't any primary data model.&nbsp; I would add that this isn't just because we haven't found it yet.&nbsp; There is not likely to be anything that we would call a primary data model.<div style="clear:both; padding-bottom:0.25em"></div>
